<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>come to a full stop • come to a stop</xh5><p> <i>come to a full stop—</i>1. stop suddenly or unexpectedly: The dog had a roll on the lawn before charging at her and <u>coming to a full</u> stop ready to play. 2. be unable to proceed any further with smth.: We have <u>come to a full stop</u> in our efforts to achieve Utopia. 3. <i>(of a narrative, etc.)</i> terminate or end abruptly: The story thus <u>comes unexpectedly to a full stop</u>.</p><p><i>come to a stop—</i>be no longer moving: The elevator <u>came to a stop</u> on the main floor.</p> </entry>
